## UI/UX Best Practices

### 1. Information Architecture

**Content Organization:**
- **Progressive disclosure** - Show essential info first, details on demand
- **Chunking** - Group related information together
- **Scannable content** - Use headings, bullets, short paragraphs
- **F-pattern** - Users scan in an F-shape, place important content accordingly
- **Z-pattern** - For landing pages and marketing content

### 2. Navigation & Wayfinding

**Navigation Principles:**
- **Consistent navigation** - Same position and behavior across pages
- **Clear current location** - Users should always know where they are
- **Breadcrumbs** - For multi-level hierarchies
- **Limited menu items** - 5-7 top-level items maximum
- **Descriptive labels** - Say what users will find, not clever names

### 3. Forms & Input

**Form Design:**
- **One column** - Easier to scan and complete
- **Logical order** - Group related fields
- **Smart defaults** - Pre-fill when possible
- **Inline validation** - Show errors immediately
- **Clear error messages** - Tell users how to fix it
- **Optional vs. required** - Mark optional fields, assume required
- **Appropriate input types** - Date pickers, dropdowns, autocomplete
- **Save progress** - For long forms, allow saving and returning

### 4. Feedback & States

**Provide Clear Feedback:**
- **Loading states** - Show progress with spinners or skeletons
- **Success states** - Confirm actions were successful
- **Error states** - Explain what went wrong and how to fix it
- **Empty states** - Guide users on what to do when there's no data
- **Disabled states** - Show why an action isn't available

### 5. Accessibility (a11y)

**Core Accessibility Requirements:**
- **Semantic HTML** - Use proper elements (button, nav, main, etc.)
- **Keyboard navigation** - All interactions work with keyboard
- **Focus indicators** - Visible focus states for keyboard users
- **Screen reader support** - Proper ARIA labels and roles
- **Color contrast** - WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1 for text)
- **Alt text** - Descriptive text for all images
- **Form labels** - Every input has an associated label
- **Skip links** - Allow skipping repetitive navigation

### 6. Mobile & Responsive

**Mobile-First Principles:**
- **Touch targets** - Minimum 44x44px for tap areas
- **Thumb-friendly** - Place important actions in easy-to-reach areas
- **Responsive breakpoints** - sm: 640px, md: 768px, lg: 1024px, xl: 1280px
- **Fluid typography** - Scale font sizes with viewport
- **Avoid hover-only** - Ensure mobile alternatives for hover interactions
- **Test on real devices** - Emulators aren't enough

### 7. Performance & Perceived Speed

**Make It Feel Fast:**
- **Skeleton screens** - Show layout while content loads
- **Optimistic UI** - Assume success, update UI immediately
- **Lazy loading** - Load images and content as needed
- **Pagination** - For large data sets
- **Debouncing** - For search and auto-save
- **Caching** - Store frequently accessed data

### 8. Content & Copy

**Writing UI Copy:**
- **Clear, not clever** - Users should understand immediately
- **Action-oriented** - Use verbs (Save, Delete, Create)
- **Consistent terminology** - Same words for same concepts
- **Concise** - Remove unnecessary words
- **Helpful error messages** - Explain the problem and solution
- **Appropriate tone** - Match your audience and context

### 9. Visual Consistency

**Design System Consistency:**
- **Component library** - shadcn/ui as foundation
- **Spacing system** - Use Tailwind spacing scale consistently
- **Color palette** - Limit colors, use consistently
- **Typography scale** - Consistent heading and text sizes
- **Icon style** - Use one icon library (lucide-react)
- **Border radius** - Consistent across all components
- **Animation timing** - Consistent transition durations

### 10. User Trust & Safety

**Build User Confidence:**
- **Confirmation for destructive actions** - Always confirm delete/remove
- **Undo functionality** - Allow reversing actions when possible
- **Clear privacy** - Explain what data is collected and why
- **Security indicators** - Show when actions are secure
- **Honest communication** - Don't hide limitations
- **Save work automatically** - Don't lose user input

